generif.text: Clinical trial of gene-disease association and gene-environment interaction. (HuGE Navigator)
this study identifies CCDC66 as a targeting factor for centrosome and cilium proteins

In-depth characterization revealed that circCCDC66 exerts its function via regulation of a subset of oncogenes, and knockdown of circCCDC66 inhibited tumor growth and cancer invasion in xenograft and orthotopic mouse models, respectively. Taken together, these findings highlight a novel oncogenic function of circRNA in cancer progression and metastasis.

Results associate a distinct retinal dystrophy phenotype with nicotinamide-nucleotide adenylyltransferase 1 protein (NMNAT1) mutation and suggest coiled-coil domain containing 66 (CCDC66) should not be considered a retinal dystrophy candidate gene.
HGF/c-Met regulates expression of SAE2 and cirRNA CCDC66 to increase epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition and drug resistance of lung adenocarcinoma cells.
this is the first report revealing that cir-CCDC66 modulates DCX expression through sponging miR-488-3p and thus participates in the onset of Hirschsprung's disease.
Circ-CCDC66 accelerates proliferation and invasion of gastric cancer via binding to miRNA-1238-3p.
Centrosomal and ciliary targeting of CCDC66 requires cooperative action of centriolar satellites, microtubules and molecular motors.
Circular RNA CCDC66 facilitates abdominal aortic aneurysm through the overexpression of CCDC66.
CircRNACCDC66 regulates cisplatin resistance in gastric cancer via the miR-618/BCL2 axis.
Circular RNA circCCDC66 promotes glioma proliferation by acting as a ceRNA for miR-320a to regulate FOXM1 expression.
Circular RNA CCDC66 Improves Murine Double Minute 4 (MDM4) Expression through Targeting miR-370 in Colorectal Cancer.
CCDC66 regulates primary cilium length and signaling via interactions with transition zone and axonemal proteins.
CCDC66 mutations are associated with high myopia through affected cell mitosis.

regulation of protein localization to cilium

name: coiled-coil domain containing 66
summary: Enables microtubule binding activity. Involved in cilium assembly; microtubule bundle formation; and regulation of protein localization to cilium. Located in several cellular components, including Flemming body; microtubule cytoskeleton; and photoreceptor inner segment. [provided by Alliance of Genome Resources, Apr 2022]
